Easy Setup Guide

1. Use Python version `3.9.13`.

2. Install Tesseract OCR.
   Download from: https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki
   After installing, add `tesseract.exe` to your system PATH.

3. Check package compatibility first:
   `pip install -r .\requirements.txt --dry-run --ignore-installed`

4. Install required packages:
   `pip install -r .\requirements.txt`

5. Install Protobuf separately:
   `pip install protobuf==3.20.3`

6. Run the project:
   - Go to `./src/`
   - Run: `python main.py`
   - Enter a username to register face
   - Sit in good lighting
   - ALIGN your FACE into WHITE BOX Properly
   - Do not press any key during face registration , it Registers Automatically

7. Optional face registration method:
   You can also add a face image manually inside the `known_faces` folder.

8. If face authentication is not working:
   - Close the app
   - Run this command to start without face auth:
     `python main.py -fd`
